Ordinarily, when sending a message to an instance for which several method signatures match, one is chosen at random and a warning is emitted. The warning is not emitted for CGFloat/NSInteger mixups. This applies to GCC 4.2, LLVM-GCC 4.2 and LLVM Compiler 1.7.

Steps to Reproduce:

#import <Foundation/Foundation.h>

@interface Unrelated
-(NSInteger)foo;
@end

@interface Obj : NSObject
@end
@implementation Obj
-(CGFloat)foo { return 124.2452; }
@end

int main (int argc, const char * argv[]) {
